    <description>Tutanota is the world's most secure email service, easy to use and private by design. Sign up for free encrypted email now.

With end-to-end encryption and 2FA, your emails have never been more secure. The built-in encryption guarantees that your mailbox belongs to you: Nobody can decrypt or read your data.

**Please Note**: This is an automatically updated package. If you find it is out of date by more than a day or two, please contact the maintainer(s) and let them know the package is no longer updating correctly.</description>
    <summary>Tutanota is an email client with a strong focus on security and privacy that lets you encrypt emails on all your devices.</summary>
    <releaseNotes># What's new
- Undo sending email action [#9543](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/9543)
 - Update DOMPurify to 3.3.2 [#10451](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10451)
- Update Electron to 40.8.0

# Bugfixes
 - `show more text` option in conversation is not visible when we enable `view in light mode` [#10412](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10412)
 - Mail editor's recipient fields contain elements that are not shown but navigable by screen readers [#10396](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10396)
 - Uncaught BadRequestError when trying to send an already scheduled mail [#10354](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10354)
 - Selecting multiple mails with active conversation grouping, shows wrong email count [#10302](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/10302)
 - Check for `structuredClone` support [#9705](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/9705)
 - Opening Notification Targets is very laggy when expanded [#4230](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/4230)
 - Undo deleting inline image does not work [#1822](https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/issues/1822)

# Milestone
https://github.com/tutao/tutanota/milestone/407?closed=1

